# apps/site — Cursor rules

Conventions for this repository are defined once and are not repeated here.

**Read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) first.** It is the single source of truth for
repo-wide rules:

- [Repository layout and commands](../../AGENTS.md#commands)
- [Feature-sliced design, naming, imports, copyright header, JSDoc](../../AGENTS.md#making-a-change)
- [Frontend conventions: accessibility, performance, state management](../../AGENTS.md#frontend)
- [Logging](../../AGENTS.md#logging)
- [Testing](../../AGENTS.md#testing)
- [Git hooks](../../AGENTS.md#git-hooks)
- [Commit and pull-request workflow](../../AGENTS.md#making-a-pull-request)

**Then read [`CLAUDE.md`](./CLAUDE.md)** for everything specific to this workspace:
tech stack and versions, directory structure, component organization,
site-specific commands, internationalization, and styling.

Two rules worth restating because getting them wrong fails CI:

- Filenames and directories are kebab-case. Identifiers (components, types,
  classes) are PascalCase. See [Naming](../../AGENTS.md#naming).
- Every source file begins with the exact header in
  [`license-header.txt`](../../license-header.txt). The
  `license-header/header` ESLint rule enforces it.

Duplicated rules drift. Pointers do not. If something here contradicts
`AGENTS.md`, `AGENTS.md` wins — fix this file.
